## ‚úÖ 1. **AgentCore Tool Schema JSON Examples**

These JSON schemas define the **tools your Bedrock Agent can call** using **AgentCore primitives** (specifically `toolUse`). You‚Äôll register these when creating your agent in the **Amazon Bedrock console** or via the API.

### üîß Tool 1: `get_runbook_from_amazon_q`
```json
{
  "toolSpec": {
    "name": "get_runbook_from_amazon_q",
    "description": "Queries Amazon Q for AWS best-practice runbooks based on an error pattern or incident description.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "json": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "query": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Natural language description of the incident (e.g., 'EC2 CPU spike after deployment')"
          }
        },
        "required": ["query"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

